1
00:00:26,793 --> 00:00:28,494
Don't get agitated.

2
00:00:31,398 --> 00:00:34,100
A Orchestra is just too good.

3
00:00:34,100 --> 00:00:35,568
You didn't expect this?

4
00:00:35,568 --> 00:00:37,804
I didn't know
they were this good.

5
00:00:37,804 --> 00:00:40,831
Do you think we can win?

6
00:00:40,831 --> 00:00:43,751
If we lose,
our orchestra will be dissolved.

7
00:00:43,751 --> 00:00:48,255
We're good too! We can win!

8
00:01:04,871 --> 00:01:06,873
Everyone, tear up your scores.

9
00:01:12,505 --> 00:01:16,876
Yes, that's how good A Orchestra is.

10
00:01:17,377 --> 00:01:19,779
The elites of Han Eum Academy of Music.

11
00:01:19,779 --> 00:01:24,876
They put a lot of effort on top of
the talents they were born with.

12
00:01:24,876 --> 00:01:30,290
Did you think you could defeat them
with only a few weeks of practice?

13
00:01:30,290 --> 00:01:31,891
Then what?

14
00:01:31,891 --> 00:01:35,027
Should we just give up?
Since we'll lose anyway?

15
00:01:35,667 --> 00:01:40,071
It's better than getting humiliated in front
of our professors, friends and families.

16
00:01:40,719 --> 00:01:42,519
How can you say
that as a conductor?

17
00:01:42,519 --> 00:01:45,054
Il Lak, stop.

18
00:01:46,339 --> 00:01:48,641
It's not just a few weeks.

19
00:01:49,443 --> 00:01:51,557
We worked really hard.

20
00:01:51,557 --> 00:01:56,388
We mastered it already,
and we have to give up now?

21
00:01:59,919 --> 00:02:01,927
I don't want to.

22
00:02:04,924 --> 00:02:08,327
I want to be on the stage.

23
00:02:09,335 --> 00:02:11,798
I know I'm not talented

24
00:02:11,798 --> 00:02:14,593
and this is my first orchestra...

25
00:02:14,593 --> 00:02:18,677
But, this is also the first time
that I practiced really hard.

26
00:02:20,507 --> 00:02:23,335
Let's do it then. Let's do it!

27
00:02:23,335 --> 00:02:24,795
Who cares if we get humiliated?

28
00:02:24,795 --> 00:02:28,821
Isn't it more humiliating not trying
anything, whether we win or lose?

29
00:02:28,821 --> 00:02:30,648
Isn't it right, Cha Yoo Jin?

30
00:02:33,111 --> 00:02:34,833
Then...

31
00:02:34,833 --> 00:02:36,962
will you trust me and follow my lead?

32
00:02:37,824 --> 00:02:39,390
Of course!

33
00:02:42,079 --> 00:02:44,381
Tear up your scores, everyone.

34
00:02:47,251 --> 00:02:49,837
We have our own weapon.

35
00:02:49,837 --> 00:02:52,339
And we still have time to rehearse.

36
00:02:53,048 --> 00:02:56,251
Let's try it. We can do it.

37
00:02:57,610 --> 00:03:00,046
Tear up your scores!
The conductor says we can do it!

38
00:03:00,046 --> 00:03:01,751
Let's go!

39
00:03:02,549 --> 00:03:04,316
Let's go!

40
00:03:24,997 --> 00:03:28,504
[Lesson 5]

41
00:03:40,262 --> 00:03:44,767
Dad! You said you were coming to
the wholesale market in Seoul today.

42
00:03:44,767 --> 00:03:49,340
After work, can you stop by
just for a while?

43
00:03:49,340 --> 00:03:51,023
We still have time left.

44
00:03:51,023 --> 00:03:52,583
I don't have time to go there.

45
00:03:52,583 --> 00:03:56,186
That instrument just eats up money.
Why would I go there to hear it?

46
00:04:03,744 --> 00:04:07,414
Min Hee! Hurry up!
Everyone is waiting.

47
00:04:07,414 --> 00:04:09,333
Okay.

48
00:04:09,333 --> 00:04:12,377
Where's Nae Il?
I thought you were together.

49
00:04:12,377 --> 00:04:14,963
I don't know
I haven't seen her.

50
00:04:14,963 --> 00:04:16,557
Really?

51
00:04:18,891 --> 00:04:23,462
Isn't she the 'mascot'?.
I'm glad she's not glued to Yoo Jin again.

52
00:04:24,806 --> 00:04:28,060
Why is von Stresemann included
on the judging panel?

53
00:04:28,060 --> 00:04:31,296
He created the special orchestra.

54
00:04:31,813 --> 00:04:35,859
The dean having the authority to choose
the judging panel was the biggest problem.

55
00:04:35,859 --> 00:04:38,793
He has nothing to do with the
two orchestras anymore...

56
00:04:38,793 --> 00:04:42,014
Besides, if there are six judges,
doesn't it mean that it'll be a tie?

57
00:04:42,582 --> 00:04:44,408
There are seven.

58
00:04:44,408 --> 00:04:47,232
There is another judge that
the dean recommended.

59
00:04:47,232 --> 00:04:50,189
We all agreed on it.

60
00:04:50,189 --> 00:04:52,000
Who is it?

61
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:57,297
We don't know
how the result will turn out.

62
00:04:57,297 --> 00:05:00,008
We'll have to leave it to them.

63
00:05:00,008 --> 00:05:03,844
They are the fairest judges.

64
00:05:13,379 --> 00:05:16,377
Girl, I looked for you everywhere...

65
00:05:20,362 --> 00:05:23,031
Long time no see, Maestro!

66
00:05:23,031 --> 00:05:26,267
It's been a while, madam.

67
00:05:26,746 --> 00:05:30,583
Yoo Jin's mom. You can call me
Yoo Jin's mom now.

68
00:05:31,456 --> 00:05:32,929
Yes.

69
00:05:34,585 --> 00:05:39,656
- Yoo Jin's mom...
- Your Korean has improved a lot!

70
00:05:40,299 --> 00:05:45,470
Well, that's why you made Yoo Jin
your assistant and had him run errands.

71
00:05:45,470 --> 00:05:47,638
Sit down, you're standing in the way.

72
00:05:48,341 --> 00:05:51,853
It's Yoo Jin's debut as a conductor.
Aren't you excited?

73
00:05:51,853 --> 00:05:53,919
Excited?

74
00:05:53,919 --> 00:05:55,546
He was busy running errands,

75
00:05:55,546 --> 00:05:57,900
I doubt that he had
much time to practice.

76
00:05:57,900 --> 00:05:59,801
Stop it.

77
00:06:00,861 --> 00:06:03,196
They're starting now.

78
00:06:13,707 --> 00:06:15,243
Thank you!

79
00:06:15,243 --> 00:06:16,700
- Here, here.
- Thank you, mister!

80
00:06:16,700 --> 00:06:19,202
Hurry up!
You shouldn't be late.

81
00:06:25,886 --> 00:06:28,096
Nae Il, you should be careful!

82
00:06:28,096 --> 00:06:29,721
- I'm sorry.
- Are you okay?

83
00:06:29,721 --> 00:06:31,479
I have to hurry...

84
00:06:33,329 --> 00:06:36,230
- Thank you.
- Hurry, hurry!

85
00:06:36,230 --> 00:06:38,732
Don't be late!

86
00:06:38,732 --> 00:06:40,700
Be careful!

87
00:06:41,443 --> 00:06:43,034
Done?

88
00:06:53,747 --> 00:06:55,449
We have 10 minutes.

89
00:06:55,449 --> 00:06:59,253
Check your instruments and attire.

90
00:07:18,397 --> 00:07:20,072
Almighty Cha,
what are you looking for?

91
00:07:20,072 --> 00:07:22,324
Water? Something to calm yourself?

92
00:07:22,324 --> 00:07:24,361
No. I feel like
I'm missing something.

93
00:07:24,361 --> 00:07:25,754
What?

94
00:07:25,754 --> 00:07:28,657
You have the baton,
the conductor's score...

95
00:07:28,657 --> 00:07:31,034
Hold on a second!

96
00:07:31,034 --> 00:07:33,972
Wait! Wait!

97
00:07:34,727 --> 00:07:37,207
Ah, Nae Il.
That's what I forgot.

98
00:07:37,207 --> 00:07:39,251
I brought our armor.

99
00:07:39,251 --> 00:07:41,503
- Our armor?
- What's our armor?

100
00:07:41,503 --> 00:07:43,170
It's...

101
00:07:44,089 --> 00:07:46,400
the special T-shirts!

102
00:07:56,209 --> 00:07:58,043
Put it away.

103
00:08:00,355 --> 00:08:02,156
Are you kidding me?

104
00:08:03,729 --> 00:08:05,944
It's not a joke.

105
00:08:05,944 --> 00:08:12,646
Look at me. I even tripped over and
got hurt because I was rushing...

106
00:08:12,646 --> 00:08:14,774
That must hurt.

107
00:08:14,774 --> 00:08:16,788
Yes, let's wear them, Cha Yoo Jin!

108
00:08:16,788 --> 00:08:21,125
It's our uniform. We'll play better
with excitement wearing them.

109
00:08:31,553 --> 00:08:34,700
Do whatever you want.
Just don't force it on me.

110
00:08:34,700 --> 00:08:38,737
- Okay! Come out, come out!
- Get your T-shirts!

111
00:08:54,952 --> 00:08:57,556
Orabang, you should wear one too.

112
00:08:57,556 --> 00:09:01,333
Orabang, I made yours extra special.

113
00:09:01,333 --> 00:09:03,360
Is this a circus?

114
00:09:04,419 --> 00:09:06,053
I'm not wearing it.

115
00:09:06,619 --> 00:09:10,155
But Orabang, I made it myself...

116
00:09:23,814 --> 00:09:26,178
They are the losers indeed.

117
00:09:26,178 --> 00:09:28,861
They don't even have the
dignity of music majors.

118
00:09:28,861 --> 00:09:32,764
I'm sorry. I should have given them a warning.

119
00:09:33,251 --> 00:09:36,601
It's a shocking surprise, as I expected.

120
00:09:37,327 --> 00:09:41,164
No one came close to Franz
when it came to shocks.

121
00:09:41,164 --> 00:09:45,201
I guess Yoo Jin
only learned to be shocking.

122
00:09:51,425 --> 00:09:53,526
Il Lak! Il Lak!

123
00:10:44,769 --> 00:10:45,938
What's with the score?

124
00:10:45,938 --> 00:10:49,408
Sorry. I thought
we should still have one.

125
00:10:50,150 --> 00:10:51,796
Let's go!

126
00:11:08,335 --> 00:11:12,198
He's the only boring one.

127
00:11:18,887 --> 00:11:21,639
At least the conductor is normal.

128
00:11:21,639 --> 00:11:23,983
He's Cha Dong Woo's son...

129
00:11:23,983 --> 00:11:26,753
He shouldn't get swayed by the losers.

130
00:11:51,128 --> 00:11:54,631
Mister, my Orabang wore
the T-shirt that I made for him.

131
00:11:54,631 --> 00:11:59,483
You're right. It was worth
getting your fingers pricked.

132
00:12:01,930 --> 00:12:05,533
Orabang, still, I made it myself...

133
00:12:22,242 --> 00:12:24,977
Cha Yoo Jin are you really okay?

134
00:12:24,977 --> 00:12:27,456
Yes, I'm fine.

135
00:12:27,456 --> 00:12:30,001
What if we lose?

136
00:12:30,001 --> 00:12:31,627
We just need to do our best

137
00:12:31,627 --> 00:12:34,003
so that we won't have
any regrets even if we lose.

138
00:12:34,003 --> 00:12:38,182
Let's show them
how hard we practiced.

139
00:12:38,182 --> 00:12:39,586
Okay.

140
00:12:40,551 --> 00:12:42,443
Let's have some fun.

141
00:12:43,395 --> 00:12:47,399
Beethoven Symphony No.3 'Eroica'

142
00:13:02,066 --> 00:13:07,226
Beethoven Symphony No. 3
Eroica, First Movement.

143
00:13:07,226 --> 00:13:11,223
Since he composed it
to dedicate it to Napoleon

144
00:13:11,223 --> 00:13:16,028
a heroic spirit is felt
in the first movement.

145
00:13:49,121 --> 00:13:53,125
Orabang is captivating everyone.

146
00:14:07,222 --> 00:14:09,375
Eroica, Fourth Movement.

147
00:14:09,375 --> 00:14:12,737
Beethoven's will to overcome
the despair of losing his hearing

148
00:14:12,737 --> 00:14:19,543
and his will for victory is shown
in the last movement of Eroica.

149
00:14:23,483 --> 00:14:25,223
Are you really going to do it?

150
00:14:25,223 --> 00:14:27,058
You wanted to have fun.

151
00:14:29,620 --> 00:14:30,679
Now!

152
00:14:30,679 --> 00:14:33,098
- Now!
- Now!

153
00:15:00,859 --> 00:15:04,541
Why did Maestro chose these people...

154
00:15:04,541 --> 00:15:06,865
Why is Yoo Il Lak the bandmaster...

155
00:15:06,865 --> 00:15:08,457
I get it now.

156
00:15:09,283 --> 00:15:11,578
A heart for enjoying music...

157
00:15:12,150 --> 00:15:16,824
They have the biggest weapon
in the world.

158
00:15:17,516 --> 00:15:21,219
Each and every one of them
are Seol Nae Il.

159
00:15:21,219 --> 00:15:25,389
My Lak is the best!
Bravo, bravo!

160
00:15:57,207 --> 00:15:59,380
You said they were the losers.

161
00:16:00,169 --> 00:16:01,988
They were.

162
00:16:04,089 --> 00:16:08,449
What on earth... changed them?

163
00:16:11,180 --> 00:16:13,473
Excuse me, you see that yellow hair?

164
00:16:13,473 --> 00:16:14,850
That's my son.

165
00:16:14,850 --> 00:16:16,226
He's my son! My son!

166
00:16:16,226 --> 00:16:19,443
Mister, it's strange.

167
00:16:20,021 --> 00:16:23,420
I feel like Orabang is getting out of reach for me.

168
00:16:30,949 --> 00:16:33,660
How come the losers are
getting so much applause?

169
00:16:33,660 --> 00:16:36,996
- Is it because of Cha Yoo Jin?
- Cha Yoo Jin Is incredible.

170
00:16:38,249 --> 00:16:40,451
What are you talking about?

171
00:16:41,043 --> 00:16:43,879
They're clapping out of pity.

172
00:16:45,690 --> 00:16:47,965
People are just too full of sympathy.

173
00:16:47,965 --> 00:16:50,943
Look at them going over the top
because they feel bad for the losers.

174
00:16:50,943 --> 00:16:54,313
Let's go out there and show them.

175
00:16:54,313 --> 00:16:57,497
Let's show them the real level
of our school orchestra.

176
00:16:58,644 --> 00:17:02,147
Okay. Everyone, do your final checks.

177
00:17:15,118 --> 00:17:19,206
- Well done, everyone!
- Good job! Good job!

178
00:17:19,206 --> 00:17:21,392
Everyone did a great job.

179
00:17:25,546 --> 00:17:27,079
Has anybody seen Seol Nae Il?

180
00:17:27,079 --> 00:17:30,700
Yeah, she should've been running
yelling 'Orabang!' by now.

181
00:17:31,718 --> 00:17:34,751
Go on ahead.
Don't leave the group.

182
00:17:34,751 --> 00:17:37,687
You said not to leave the group.
But where are you going?

183
00:17:40,519 --> 00:17:42,921
Yoo Jin, good job!

184
00:17:48,569 --> 00:17:50,123
Father!

185
00:17:50,123 --> 00:17:52,572
My son!

186
00:17:58,537 --> 00:18:00,993
Father, did you see me?
Weren't I the best?

187
00:18:00,993 --> 00:18:02,662
My soul dominated everything!

188
00:18:02,662 --> 00:18:05,794
Yes, yes you did.

189
00:18:05,794 --> 00:18:09,360
My son led an orchestra
as a bandmaster...

190
00:18:11,925 --> 00:18:14,848
Your mom should've seen this...

191
00:18:15,721 --> 00:18:17,648
Are you crying, Dad?

192
00:18:17,648 --> 00:18:20,304
Your nose is running...

193
00:18:23,478 --> 00:18:25,312
Il Lak...

194
00:18:26,940 --> 00:18:28,868
My son...

195
00:18:40,579 --> 00:18:41,960
Dad!

196
00:18:45,459 --> 00:18:47,559
When did you get here?

197
00:18:47,559 --> 00:18:50,402
Did you see my performance?

198
00:18:50,402 --> 00:18:51,858
I did.

199
00:18:52,498 --> 00:18:54,366
You told me to come!

200
00:18:54,885 --> 00:18:58,421
That contrabass is big for
nothing, eating up money...

201
00:18:59,452 --> 00:19:01,353
You really can't give it up?

202
00:19:01,980 --> 00:19:03,711
I'm sorry.

203
00:19:14,446 --> 00:19:15,489
Dad...

204
00:19:15,489 --> 00:19:19,760
It's worthless, you can't even eat it.
It's just damn expensive...

205
00:19:28,827 --> 00:19:30,484
The sound...

206
00:19:31,783 --> 00:19:34,532
The sound of it was really nice to listen to.

207
00:19:35,634 --> 00:19:38,293
That's why you can't give up.

208
00:19:42,850 --> 00:19:44,323
Get back in.

209
00:19:48,580 --> 00:19:51,542
Dad, make sure to wear your hat.

210
00:19:51,542 --> 00:19:53,819
You'll get sunburned!

211
00:19:53,819 --> 00:19:57,430
Make sure to eat even if
you don't have appetite.

212
00:20:00,242 --> 00:20:01,886
Bye.

213
00:20:39,104 --> 00:20:41,533
Dvorak Symphony No. 9, 'From the New World'

214
00:20:41,533 --> 00:20:44,569
Dvorak Symphony No.9 'From the New World.'

215
00:20:45,517 --> 00:20:47,759
Dvorak from Bohemia composed this

216
00:20:47,759 --> 00:20:51,625
while he was the director of the National
Conservatory of Music of America.

217
00:20:51,625 --> 00:20:55,140
It is one of the most famous
symphonies in history.

218
00:20:55,140 --> 00:20:59,725
The first movement starts off slowly and
picks up its tempo in a lively way.

219
00:20:59,725 --> 00:21:03,124
The second movement starts
with a chorus of wind instruments

220
00:21:03,124 --> 00:21:06,427
and continues on with the melody
of the English horn.

221
00:21:42,511 --> 00:21:46,175
Majestic and elegant like this...

222
00:21:47,029 --> 00:21:50,652
No, Cha Yoo Jin would have
gone with fullness.

223
00:21:55,981 --> 00:21:58,183
His conducting is shaky.

224
00:22:03,198 --> 00:22:04,770
What's wrong with his conducting?

225
00:22:04,770 --> 00:22:06,771
Get back to your pace!

226
00:22:11,999 --> 00:22:15,602
That kid saw Cha Yoo Jin conducting.

227
00:22:27,347 --> 00:22:28,913
I missed it.

228
00:22:33,520 --> 00:22:34,771
Keep it up.

229
00:22:34,771 --> 00:22:36,600
Don't get confused, everyone.

230
00:22:47,065 --> 00:22:50,644
Why isn't anyone looking at me?
You should watch me and perform!

231
00:22:50,644 --> 00:22:53,046
Come to your senses, please!

232
00:23:31,662 --> 00:23:35,999
As expected the elite's orchestra is different.

233
00:23:37,334 --> 00:23:41,103
That kid is... intimidated.

234
00:23:41,720 --> 00:23:44,055
That's what having talent is.

235
00:23:44,055 --> 00:23:48,152
It makes the effort and time useless.

236
00:24:38,560 --> 00:24:40,458
Why are you here alone?

237
00:24:40,458 --> 00:24:41,940
What about your members?

238
00:24:41,940 --> 00:24:43,841
Professor Ahn...

239
00:24:44,723 --> 00:24:47,024
You came to play the piano.

240
00:24:48,112 --> 00:24:51,756
If it was a piano performance today,
you and Yoo Jin would've played together.

241
00:24:51,756 --> 00:24:56,877
- It's a bit disappointing.
- I'll play with them next time.

242
00:24:58,270 --> 00:25:00,030
Nae Il.

243
00:25:00,030 --> 00:25:04,726
You have to get proper lessons from
now on if you want to play with Yoo Jin.

244
00:25:04,726 --> 00:25:07,196
You can't keep playing
the fart song forever.

245
00:25:07,196 --> 00:25:10,287
Why not? The fart song is fun.

246
00:25:10,287 --> 00:25:15,540
You also told me that it's the best
music when I have fun playing it.

247
00:25:15,540 --> 00:25:17,938
Don't you want to play better?

248
00:25:17,938 --> 00:25:19,853
You have talent.

249
00:25:19,853 --> 00:25:23,341
You can enter competitions
and win awards...

250
00:25:23,341 --> 00:25:26,443
I said I'm not entering
any competitions!

251
00:25:37,329 --> 00:25:40,613
I'm going to be a
kindergarten teacher anyway...

252
00:25:41,359 --> 00:25:44,287
So what's the point of
entering competitions?

253
00:25:44,287 --> 00:25:48,257
I'm going to play the piano and
have fun with kids everyday.

254
00:25:48,257 --> 00:25:50,384
Have fun just like kids...

255
00:25:50,384 --> 00:25:51,840
Do you...

256
00:25:51,840 --> 00:25:54,280
Really want to become
a kindergarten teacher?

257
00:25:54,280 --> 00:25:57,705
Or do you want to continue playing
the piano by doing so?

258
00:25:58,350 --> 00:25:59,854
Pardon?

259
00:26:00,602 --> 00:26:04,759
Nae Il, you can't be a kid forever.

260
00:26:11,823 --> 00:26:15,026
You're a bit strange today, Professor.

261
00:26:16,468 --> 00:26:19,918
I should get going. Bye now.

262
00:26:37,097 --> 00:26:40,399
What's wrong with living
like a kid forever?

263
00:26:42,895 --> 00:26:45,230
You told me yourself...

264
00:26:45,863 --> 00:26:48,740
that having fun is the best.

265
00:26:59,786 --> 00:27:04,148
Nae Il, did something happen?

266
00:27:04,148 --> 00:27:08,686
Orabang, I'm really sad.

267
00:27:08,686 --> 00:27:10,923
I'm upset.

268
00:27:12,174 --> 00:27:15,444
Come here,
I'll make you feel better.

269
00:27:18,347 --> 00:27:19,640
Did you make them kiss?

270
00:27:19,640 --> 00:27:22,375
No, I let him give her a hug.

271
00:27:23,628 --> 00:27:25,463
That's the same thing.

272
00:27:28,647 --> 00:27:31,318
I knew it.
It still remains like this.

273
00:27:31,318 --> 00:27:33,203
Orabang...

274
00:27:34,780 --> 00:27:38,162
Your fingers are pricked
and your knee is scraped.

275
00:27:38,162 --> 00:27:41,286
What's this?
You should've been careful!

276
00:27:41,286 --> 00:27:42,966
I'm sorry.

277
00:27:44,414 --> 00:27:45,801
Thanks to you,

278
00:27:45,801 --> 00:27:48,020
I had fun at the performance.

279
00:27:50,420 --> 00:27:52,130
Ouch.

280
00:27:52,130 --> 00:27:53,581
Does it hurt?

281
00:27:59,888 --> 00:28:03,225
Orabang, you're really close.

282
00:28:03,225 --> 00:28:05,101
Stop with the nonsense.

283
00:28:09,064 --> 00:28:14,237
Orabang, I got hurt here, too.
Can you blow here, too?

284
00:28:14,237 --> 00:28:16,293
- Where?
- Here.

285
00:28:17,014 --> 00:28:18,520
Go to the doctor.

286
00:28:19,700 --> 00:28:23,837
You're the real medicine,
so just once.

287
00:28:25,529 --> 00:28:27,088
Declined!

288
00:28:32,713 --> 00:28:34,651
Thank you.

289
00:28:57,528 --> 00:29:00,199
So the audience decision is S.

290
00:29:00,199 --> 00:29:01,838
Is that right?

291
00:29:03,368 --> 00:29:06,304
Is that also what you think,
Professor Do?

292
00:29:07,414 --> 00:29:08,951
Yes.

293
00:29:09,701 --> 00:29:11,235
But...

294
00:29:13,003 --> 00:29:15,914
A Orchestra was technically much better.

295
00:29:15,914 --> 00:29:18,189
That's right.

296
00:29:18,189 --> 00:29:20,725
It's an extraordinary orchestra.

297
00:29:20,725 --> 00:29:26,564
To play that well in that situation,
they must've practiced a lot.

298
00:29:26,564 --> 00:29:36,407
It's just that the audience chose
an enjoyable orchestra over technique.

299
00:29:39,488 --> 00:29:41,112
That's right.

300
00:29:46,631 --> 00:29:49,908
Now I'm going to tell you
the result of the votes.

301
00:29:56,421 --> 00:29:58,423
A Orchestra...

302
00:29:59,049 --> 00:30:00,639
Three votes.

303
00:30:02,594 --> 00:30:04,828
S Orchestra...

304
00:30:06,515 --> 00:30:08,349
Two votes.

305
00:30:09,852 --> 00:30:13,071
It's a tie if you include
the audience vote.

306
00:30:13,071 --> 00:30:14,451
But...

307
00:30:14,451 --> 00:30:16,941
Someone didn't vote.

308
00:30:20,839 --> 00:30:23,141
Professor von Stresemann.

309
00:30:31,990 --> 00:30:37,862
I believe Maestro will make
a wise decision.

310
00:30:44,970 --> 00:30:47,026
So...

311
00:30:47,026 --> 00:30:49,641
I have to make a decision.

312
00:31:13,665 --> 00:31:15,959
I don't know
how to deliver the news...

313
00:31:15,959 --> 00:31:20,796
Professors' votes went to you, of course.

314
00:31:21,340 --> 00:31:26,396
Professor von Stresemann
was supposed to cast the last vote.

315
00:31:26,396 --> 00:31:30,467
Which one did he vote for?

316
00:31:34,436 --> 00:31:36,229
Which one is it?

317
00:31:38,315 --> 00:31:40,209
He didn't vote...

318
00:31:44,029 --> 00:31:45,819
He ran away.

319
00:32:05,348 --> 00:32:08,095
How odd can you possibly be! Franz!

320
00:32:08,095 --> 00:32:09,513
[I'm going to the Yoon Yi Song Music Festival]

321
00:32:09,513 --> 00:32:11,974
This habit of running away
when he's cornered...

322
00:32:11,974 --> 00:32:14,165
It started again!

323
00:32:14,165 --> 00:32:17,270
I want to see you, Franz.

324
00:32:19,940 --> 00:32:23,645
Now, cheers to S Orchestra!

325
00:32:23,645 --> 00:32:28,216
S Oche, S Oche, S Oche!

326
00:32:35,247 --> 00:32:37,414
Our Lak is the best!
Help yourselves!

327
00:32:37,414 --> 00:32:40,811
- Enjoy!
- Thank you!

328
00:32:40,811 --> 00:32:45,547
Orabang, drink just a little.
Fill up with food.

329
00:32:45,547 --> 00:32:48,093
- You did very well today.
- Enjoy.

330
00:32:48,093 --> 00:32:49,879
What happens to us now?

331
00:32:49,879 --> 00:32:53,915
If the professor doesn't come back, do
we continue with A and S Orchestras?

332
00:32:54,399 --> 00:32:56,807
I hope he doesn't come back.

333
00:32:56,807 --> 00:33:01,445
I agree. Almighty Cha is enough
as our conductor.

334
00:33:07,585 --> 00:33:09,559
[Chae Do Kyung]

335
00:33:10,199 --> 00:33:12,723
Yes, I arrived this morning.

336
00:33:12,723 --> 00:33:15,204
I came back in time for your
conducting debut.

337
00:33:15,204 --> 00:33:16,914
Of course I have to see it.

338
00:33:16,914 --> 00:33:19,516
It's been a while.
Let's go for a drink.

339
00:33:21,032 --> 00:33:22,453
Why not?

340
00:33:24,671 --> 00:33:26,284
Where?

341
00:33:27,090 --> 00:33:29,461
You're at an after-party? You?

342
00:33:32,346 --> 00:33:33,711
Where were you?

343
00:33:33,711 --> 00:33:35,439
I'll be there soon.

344
00:33:39,186 --> 00:33:40,879
Were you waiting for me?

345
00:33:40,879 --> 00:33:42,172
Of course.

346
00:33:42,172 --> 00:33:45,143
Let's go somewhere and have a drink.

347
00:33:45,143 --> 00:33:46,877
Seung Oh...

348
00:33:47,986 --> 00:33:50,280
I want to stand as the best.

349
00:33:50,280 --> 00:33:53,198
- What?
- If I can't be the best...

350
00:33:53,198 --> 00:33:56,200
then I need to at least
stand next to the best.

351
00:33:56,995 --> 00:34:02,084
Our families are friends, you're
not going to be clinging, are you?

352
00:34:02,084 --> 00:34:05,355
We've been good friends.

353
00:34:05,355 --> 00:34:09,625
I have plans, so I should go.

354
00:34:14,054 --> 00:34:15,855
Do Kyung...

355
00:34:26,692 --> 00:34:28,385
You're so noisy, Yoo Il Lak!

356
00:34:28,385 --> 00:34:31,489
You're obviously a violinist,
making that annoying noise.

357
00:34:31,489 --> 00:34:33,816
You're a born timpani player.

358
00:34:33,816 --> 00:34:36,535
You get upset over nothing.

359
00:34:36,535 --> 00:34:40,304
You think you can play
without timpani?

360
00:34:40,304 --> 00:34:42,747
Timpani is the best!

361
00:34:42,747 --> 00:34:45,375
- Are you laughing at wind instruments?
- He's right!

362
00:34:45,375 --> 00:34:50,085
You can hide yourself, but we get
pointed out as soon as we make a mistake.

363
00:34:53,231 --> 00:34:57,493
Everyone, line up behind me.
For instruments, the bigger the better.

364
00:34:57,493 --> 00:34:59,924
Contrabass is the best!

365
00:35:05,022 --> 00:35:08,284
Hey hey Nae Il, what's with
your meddling here?

366
00:35:08,284 --> 00:35:10,378
Lak, get out of this!

367
00:35:10,378 --> 00:35:12,445
Seriously...

368
00:35:19,049 --> 00:35:20,851
Hello.

369
00:35:21,830 --> 00:35:24,258
Can I interrupt for a minute?

370
00:35:24,258 --> 00:35:26,185
Please have a seat here.

371
00:35:26,185 --> 00:35:28,112
Sit down, sit down!

372
00:35:28,112 --> 00:35:31,242
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

373
00:35:33,926 --> 00:35:36,400
You look like you're having fun.

374
00:35:36,400 --> 00:35:39,603
This is why you said no
when I asked you out on a date?

375
00:35:52,400 --> 00:35:54,882
Move, this is my seat.

376
00:35:54,882 --> 00:35:56,696
Move!

377
00:35:56,696 --> 00:35:59,131
Who the heck is she?

378
00:35:59,131 --> 00:36:00,494
Nae Il!

379
00:36:00,494 --> 00:36:04,309
The right side is hers
and the left is mine.

380
00:36:04,309 --> 00:36:06,644
And who the heck is he?

381
00:36:07,125 --> 00:36:09,961
Who are they? Friends?

382
00:36:12,339 --> 00:36:15,050
I'm sorry, but I'm Orabang's wife.

383
00:36:15,050 --> 00:36:17,863
I think you're out of line.

384
00:36:17,863 --> 00:36:18,995
Orabang...

385
00:36:18,995 --> 00:36:20,889
- That's not right.
- Please tell her.

386
00:36:20,889 --> 00:36:23,458
Hey, stop it now.

387
00:36:26,311 --> 00:36:29,080
Cha Yoo Jin's still popular.

388
00:36:32,192 --> 00:36:34,661
Do you have sore throat?
Do you want to head out first?

389
00:36:35,747 --> 00:36:39,490
No. I was curious
about your members.

390
00:36:40,492 --> 00:36:44,243
It's been a while.
It's nice to be here.

391
00:36:44,243 --> 00:36:47,679
Chae Do Kyung, you used to
hate parties like this.

392
00:36:48,227 --> 00:36:51,086
You're the one who changed.

393
00:36:51,086 --> 00:36:54,219
You're more attractive this way.

394
00:36:54,219 --> 00:36:56,599
You're really pretty.

395
00:36:56,599 --> 00:36:59,290
Miss Han Eum is indeed different.

396
00:36:59,290 --> 00:37:00,758
Thank you.

397
00:37:05,934 --> 00:37:08,601
- Who are you looking for?
- Nae Il.

398
00:37:08,601 --> 00:37:11,048
She's been helping with serving
the whole time and hasn't eaten yet.

399
00:37:11,048 --> 00:37:12,566
Where did she go,
leaving the food behind?

400
00:37:12,566 --> 00:37:13,921
Nae Il?

401
00:37:13,921 --> 00:37:16,965
The girl... just now?

402
00:37:17,529 --> 00:37:19,198
Nae Il left.

403
00:37:19,198 --> 00:37:20,741
She did?

404
00:37:20,741 --> 00:37:23,208
What's the occasion for leaving
all the food behind?

405
00:37:26,079 --> 00:37:28,781
You told me everyday
not to get close to you!

406
00:37:29,791 --> 00:37:32,627
You didn't say anything
to Miss Han Eum!

407
00:37:33,879 --> 00:37:37,716
You're not allowed to come
close to me either, Orabang!

408
00:37:57,068 --> 00:37:59,128
I'm sorry.

409
00:38:09,581 --> 00:38:12,953
Let's go. You'll catch cold if
you stay here longer.

410
00:38:14,795 --> 00:38:17,262
I drank too much,
so I'm leaving now.

411
00:38:19,077 --> 00:38:21,019
See you next time.

412
00:38:21,019 --> 00:38:22,474
Bye.

413
00:38:22,474 --> 00:38:25,878
- Are you really leaving?
- Where are you going?

414
00:38:25,878 --> 00:38:27,933
Where are you going?

415
00:38:27,933 --> 00:38:31,336
- We're going for a second round!
- We're going for a third round, too!

416
00:38:45,242 --> 00:38:48,213
This is all I can do for you
as your ex-boyfriend.

417
00:38:48,213 --> 00:38:50,539
- Yoo Jin..
- You can go by yourself, right?

418
00:38:50,539 --> 00:38:51,925
Bye.

419
00:38:53,542 --> 00:38:55,310
Yoo Jin!

420
00:39:11,190 --> 00:39:12,798
I got you!

421
00:39:14,980 --> 00:39:16,285
Does it hurt?

422
00:39:29,953 --> 00:39:35,225
There you go again. I see Orabang
everyday, so what's happening to me?

423
00:39:36,919 --> 00:39:38,431
Nae Il!

424
00:39:39,588 --> 00:39:41,106
Seol Nae Il!

425
00:39:43,509 --> 00:39:45,367
No!

426
00:39:45,367 --> 00:39:49,482
I'm only Nae Il to Orabang.
I'm not Seol Nae Il!

427
00:39:52,684 --> 00:39:55,965
Mom, it's really strange.

428
00:39:56,477 --> 00:39:58,542
Am I sick?

429
00:39:59,274 --> 00:40:00,945
Seol Nae Il!

430
00:40:10,494 --> 00:40:12,622
She's not home yet?

431
00:40:17,125 --> 00:40:20,337
Let's have fun so that
Yoo Jin will get jealous!

432
00:40:20,337 --> 00:40:26,368
Second round! Second round!

433
00:40:26,368 --> 00:40:31,131
Forget about Miss Han Eum!
It's just the make-up she has!

434
00:40:31,131 --> 00:40:36,875
I won't exchange you even for
a truckload of those girls.

435
00:40:36,875 --> 00:40:40,760
- Let's go for the second round, Min Hee!
- Let's go!

436
00:40:42,192 --> 00:40:47,864
I'll head home now. I have a
part-time job tomorrow morning.

437
00:40:48,991 --> 00:40:53,453
I had fun today. See you tomorrow.

438
00:40:53,453 --> 00:40:54,988
Bye.

439
00:41:01,503 --> 00:41:05,327
Was Min Hee always that pretty?

440
00:41:05,327 --> 00:41:06,733
Right?

441
00:41:06,733 --> 00:41:09,967
She was always soaked in sweat
carrying that contrabass

442
00:41:09,967 --> 00:41:12,068
so I didn't notice.

443
00:41:12,639 --> 00:41:15,573
Does Min Hee have a boyfriend?

444
00:41:15,573 --> 00:41:18,202
I don't think she does.

445
00:41:22,649 --> 00:41:26,945
Second round! Second round!

446
00:41:26,945 --> 00:41:29,806
- Let's go in! Let's go in!
- Let's go there!

447
00:41:29,806 --> 00:41:32,365
Wait, wait!

448
00:41:32,365 --> 00:41:33,950
I don't think we should go there.

449
00:41:33,950 --> 00:41:35,913
- Why not? It's close!
- Let's go there!

450
00:41:35,913 --> 00:41:39,634
No, since we won today,
let's go to a better place.

451
00:41:39,634 --> 00:41:41,928
It's on me!

452
00:41:41,928 --> 00:41:44,796
- Really?
- Let's go!

453
00:41:44,796 --> 00:41:50,188
Second round! Second round!

454
00:41:50,188 --> 00:41:54,014
Second round! Second round!

455
00:41:57,449 --> 00:41:59,732
Excuse me.

456
00:41:59,732 --> 00:42:02,314
The elite bandmaster
drinks soju, too?

457
00:42:02,314 --> 00:42:04,816
I thought you're more
of a wine person.

458
00:42:04,816 --> 00:42:08,352
Hey, do you have something to say?
If not, just leave.

459
00:42:14,034 --> 00:42:16,502
You know we won today.

460
00:42:18,664 --> 00:42:22,969
I was the one who fell,
but our orchestra didn't.

461
00:42:22,969 --> 00:42:24,626
I know.

462
00:42:25,587 --> 00:42:28,186
You guys were great.

463
00:42:28,186 --> 00:42:30,655
I'm sorry for looking down on you.

464
00:42:30,655 --> 00:42:32,645
We're a little...

465
00:42:32,645 --> 00:42:35,097
Really great.

466
00:42:35,097 --> 00:42:37,799
I'm glad you realized it now.

467
00:42:39,434 --> 00:42:41,157
I accept.

468
00:42:41,854 --> 00:42:44,536
I hope we get another chance
to compete.

469
00:42:44,536 --> 00:42:49,427
We will do our best and
not be arrogant then.

470
00:43:01,623 --> 00:43:03,558
She has a wild side.

471
00:43:05,127 --> 00:43:06,844
She's pretty.

472
00:43:27,439 --> 00:43:31,282
I don't think Nae Il is in the mood
for a lesson today.

473
00:43:31,282 --> 00:43:34,529
You're right, Professor.
I'm depressed.

474
00:43:34,529 --> 00:43:37,088
Should I give you a news
that will make you feel better?

475
00:43:37,088 --> 00:43:39,198
What is it?

476
00:43:39,198 --> 00:43:41,399
Cha Yoo Jin will be here soon.

477
00:43:42,581 --> 00:43:45,000
I should get going, Professor.

478
00:43:45,000 --> 00:43:47,836
Why? Did you argue with Yoo Jin?

479
00:43:48,560 --> 00:43:51,963
No, it's not that...

480
00:43:53,011 --> 00:43:56,074
But I can't face Yoo Jin right now.

481
00:43:56,074 --> 00:43:57,878
Why not?

482
00:43:58,764 --> 00:44:02,976
I'm just... disappointed about last night.

483
00:44:02,976 --> 00:44:04,570
Anyway!

484
00:44:04,570 --> 00:44:08,740
Yoo Jin always disappoints you,
but you've still been cheerful.

485
00:44:09,621 --> 00:44:12,653
You're right, I was.

486
00:44:12,653 --> 00:44:14,613
Then why, all of a sudden?

487
00:44:14,613 --> 00:44:17,266
I don't know either.

488
00:44:20,244 --> 00:44:22,187
It's about time.

489
00:44:23,830 --> 00:44:25,397
Pardon?

490
00:44:28,666 --> 00:44:31,438
What did he mean by,
'it's about time'?

491
00:44:32,548 --> 00:44:35,338
Professor Ahn is strange sometimes.

492
00:44:59,825 --> 00:45:01,801
Jackpot.

493
00:45:01,801 --> 00:45:04,663
I thought I wouldn't
get to see him today.

494
00:45:09,989 --> 00:45:11,515
You should've been here
just a bit sooner.

495
00:45:11,515 --> 00:45:13,589
Then you'd have seen Nae Il.

496
00:45:13,589 --> 00:45:16,341
I haven't seen her all day.

497
00:45:16,341 --> 00:45:17,908
Is that right?

498
00:45:19,178 --> 00:45:22,360
It's spring time. How nice.

499
00:45:22,360 --> 00:45:24,195
It's fall.

500
00:45:25,536 --> 00:45:29,039
Is it impossible for me to change
my major to conducting?

501
00:45:29,521 --> 00:45:32,229
- Come to think of it, you're still a piano major.
- Yes.

502
00:45:32,229 --> 00:45:35,819
The application period is already past due,
so I'm wondering if there's another way.

503
00:45:35,819 --> 00:45:37,707
Professor Ahn!

504
00:45:38,488 --> 00:45:42,133
Did you know about this, Professor Ahn?

505
00:45:42,133 --> 00:45:44,715
Did you plot this together,
by any chance?

506
00:45:44,715 --> 00:45:47,623
- What do you mean?
- Yoon Yi Song Music Festival!

507
00:45:47,623 --> 00:45:51,719
Yoon Yi Song Music Festival...
Professor Stresemann is there, isn't he?

508
00:45:51,719 --> 00:45:53,571
We received an official notice.

509
00:45:53,571 --> 00:45:57,108
The recommendation for students
who will attend the master class!

510
00:46:01,833 --> 00:46:03,276
Who?

511
00:46:05,307 --> 00:46:08,013
- Me?
- Not just you!

512
00:46:09,269 --> 00:46:11,188
Even Ma Su Min and Yoo Il Lak!

513
00:46:11,188 --> 00:46:13,404
The forever flunker Yoo Il Lak!

514
00:46:13,404 --> 00:46:15,940
That, I can understand.

515
00:46:15,940 --> 00:46:20,050
But how can we send a student who plays
the fart song to the master class?

516
00:46:20,050 --> 00:46:23,825
It's intended to humiliate
our school internationally!

517
00:46:23,825 --> 00:46:25,560
- Seol Nae Il too?
- Seol Nae Il, too?

518
00:46:30,221 --> 00:46:32,468
You're Seol Nae Il?

519
00:46:32,468 --> 00:46:35,844
You're the one
who came for the job interview?

520
00:46:35,844 --> 00:46:39,091
Yes, that's me.

521
00:46:39,091 --> 00:46:42,971
Leaving out so many talented people
who applied for the master class...

522
00:46:42,971 --> 00:46:45,785
and handing that precious opportunity
to that fart song player?

523
00:46:45,785 --> 00:46:47,391
I cannot accept this!

524
00:46:47,391 --> 00:46:51,812
But if Maestro von Stresemann
already recommended them...

525
00:46:51,812 --> 00:46:53,853
No way!

526
00:46:53,853 --> 00:46:55,941
You scared me.

527
00:46:55,941 --> 00:47:01,480
This time, we must send a clear
message about von Stresemann's oddity.

528
00:47:05,457 --> 00:47:08,829
[Damn Old Coot]
I'll tell you who played the piano...

529
00:47:08,829 --> 00:47:11,623
so send the students that I recommended.

530
00:47:11,623 --> 00:47:13,593
Did you...

531
00:47:13,593 --> 00:47:16,676
tell von Stresemann
I was looking for the student,

532
00:47:16,676 --> 00:47:18,755
who was playing 'Eroica'?

533
00:47:18,755 --> 00:47:20,141
Yes.

534
00:47:20,141 --> 00:47:23,594
You said you had to find that student, so...

535
00:47:23,594 --> 00:47:25,974
This damn old coot!

536
00:47:26,805 --> 00:47:30,350
The fart song,
out of all the people!

537
00:47:30,350 --> 00:47:35,279
You want me to give that precious chance
to a student who plays the fart song?

538
00:47:38,775 --> 00:47:40,152
That's what happened!

539
00:47:40,152 --> 00:47:42,667
I really thought you were
a married student couple.

540
00:47:42,667 --> 00:47:44,823
So you're from Jeju Island.

541
00:47:44,823 --> 00:47:48,206
Your dad has a pony farm
and your mom is a shell fish diver?

542
00:47:48,206 --> 00:47:52,677
That's amazing.
You must have a knack for living.

543
00:47:53,624 --> 00:47:55,785
What about siblings?
Are you alone?

544
00:47:55,785 --> 00:47:57,233
Yes.

545
00:47:58,128 --> 00:48:02,299
An only child with an only child...
That's pretty good, too.

546
00:48:04,635 --> 00:48:06,970
Which Sul clan are you?
What's your date of birth?

547
00:48:06,970 --> 00:48:08,737
And time you were born?

548
00:48:12,267 --> 00:48:17,035
By the way, Mini Min Hee's boss...

549
00:48:17,035 --> 00:48:20,338
I don't know what
you're talking about now...

550
00:48:21,446 --> 00:48:24,848
I should at least know
these information about you.

551
00:49:03,318 --> 00:49:06,149
Why is the house so clean?

552
00:49:07,950 --> 00:49:10,517
Now I am hallucinating...

553
00:49:10,517 --> 00:49:11,672
I'm tired.

554
00:49:11,672 --> 00:49:13,793
You made a mess already?

555
00:49:16,164 --> 00:49:20,175
You can't throw out old things..
you pick up things from the street..

556
00:49:20,175 --> 00:49:21,982
That's why your place is a mess!

557
00:49:21,982 --> 00:49:23,961
How did you get in here?

558
00:49:23,961 --> 00:49:26,353
How did you know the code to my place?

559
00:49:26,353 --> 00:49:28,591
It was the same as mine.

560
00:49:28,591 --> 00:49:31,892
Anyway, a single lady lives here alone...

561
00:49:31,892 --> 00:49:35,222
- This is a crime!
- Are you in any position to say that?

562
00:49:35,222 --> 00:49:37,561
You trespass my place
and steal my food all the time!

563
00:49:37,561 --> 00:49:39,975
I was just supporting you...

564
00:49:46,486 --> 00:49:50,523
Now Chae Do Kyung will be
doing that, right?

565
00:49:51,806 --> 00:49:54,241
Why are you bringing up Chae Do Kyung?

566
00:49:54,912 --> 00:49:57,748
She wouldn't be supporting her
ex-boyfriend anyway.

567
00:49:58,418 --> 00:50:00,887
Ex-boyfriend?

568
00:50:09,882 --> 00:50:13,013
Orabang, by the way, what's this?

569
00:50:13,844 --> 00:50:16,940
Is it a so-called 'gift of love'?

570
00:50:16,940 --> 00:50:19,141
I told you not to get
ahead of yourself.

571
00:50:20,274 --> 00:50:22,275
I picked it up on the way here.

572
00:50:22,759 --> 00:50:25,984
Why are you so careless
with your hands?

573
00:50:25,984 --> 00:50:28,334
It got cold, so carry it with you.

574
00:50:28,334 --> 00:50:30,469
Yes, Orabang.

575
00:50:31,785 --> 00:50:34,454
Is there something between us now?

576
00:50:37,412 --> 00:50:40,360
You're invited to the master class
at Yoon Yi Song Music Festival.

577
00:50:40,360 --> 00:50:43,596
We're leaving next week,
so get ready.

578
00:50:48,045 --> 00:50:51,880
You don't know about
Yoon Yi Song Music Festival?

579
00:50:51,880 --> 00:50:56,095
Every year, the best musicians
give lessons and have performances.

580
00:50:56,095 --> 00:50:58,245
This is the most well-recognized
music festival in the country.

581
00:50:58,245 --> 00:51:01,016
I don't know and I'm not going.

582
00:51:01,016 --> 00:51:04,398
I'm going to be with you forever, Orabang.

583
00:51:06,286 --> 00:51:09,221
Fine, forget it if you don't want it.

584
00:51:09,221 --> 00:51:10,876
I'm going.

585
00:51:12,926 --> 00:51:15,395
- Are you going?
- Why do you care?

586
00:51:15,395 --> 00:51:18,625
- You said you weren't going.
- When did I say I wasn't?

587
00:51:18,625 --> 00:51:20,163
You have foul intentions.

588
00:51:20,163 --> 00:51:22,121
You have no right to go to
the master class.

589
00:51:22,121 --> 00:51:24,471
I shouldn't miss it if you're going.

590
00:51:24,471 --> 00:51:28,475
Let me have it. Let me take a look.
Yoon Yi Song Music Festival...

591
00:51:30,299 --> 00:51:33,735
Let's go!

592
00:51:35,148 --> 00:51:38,485
- Il Lak I Go Go!
- Il Lak, let's go!

593
00:51:38,485 --> 00:51:41,688
Orabang, kimbap is the best
when going on a trip. Try one?

594
00:51:41,688 --> 00:51:45,844
What are you saying?
I brought almonds for Almighty Cha!

595
00:51:48,695 --> 00:51:52,299
Hey, I prepared it for Almighty Cha...

596
00:51:52,299 --> 00:51:54,698
Be quiet, you idiots!

597
00:51:54,698 --> 00:51:57,910
Hey, aren't you nervous about
going to the music festival?

598
00:51:57,910 --> 00:52:00,278
Let me get some sleep, please!

599
00:52:05,112 --> 00:52:09,949
Orabang, it's time to get out.
Wake up.

600
00:52:10,784 --> 00:52:12,352
Orabang!

601
00:52:17,291 --> 00:52:19,325
Are we at a rest area?

602
00:52:22,748 --> 00:52:23,977
What's this?

603
00:52:23,977 --> 00:52:26,495
Water park!

604
00:52:27,467 --> 00:52:32,572
My best friend, a man who only studies
is not attractive in the 21st century.

605
00:52:34,026 --> 00:52:35,976
Memories at a water park
with Almighty Cha!

606
00:52:35,976 --> 00:52:38,378
I'll remember it for
the rest of my life.

607
00:52:38,378 --> 00:52:42,076
This is your swimsuit.
I prepared it for you.

608
00:52:42,076 --> 00:52:44,581
I get sunburned easily.

609
00:52:44,581 --> 00:52:46,083
It's not summer anymore.

610
00:52:46,083 --> 00:52:49,503
No! Just hang out without me.
I'll stay in the car.

611
00:52:49,503 --> 00:52:52,878
Orabang, you just want to
stay in the car with me.

612
00:52:52,878 --> 00:52:56,096
Okay, let's get cozy in the car...

613
00:52:56,096 --> 00:52:58,398
- Wake up.
- Have fun!

614
00:52:59,093 --> 00:53:01,034
Do you have a body secret?

615
00:53:01,034 --> 00:53:04,704
A mole on your belly button...
or belly fat?

616
00:53:05,474 --> 00:53:06,606
Ducky butt.

617
00:53:06,606 --> 00:53:08,108
What are you imagining?

618
00:53:08,108 --> 00:53:12,648
You can't get back in the car.
No money, no key...

619
00:53:12,648 --> 00:53:16,697
Or you can just wait in the parking lot
until we come back.

620
00:53:20,087 --> 00:53:22,384
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

621
00:53:23,245 --> 00:53:25,433
Hurry up, Orabang!

622
00:53:43,932 --> 00:53:45,733
Nae Il! Nae Il!

623
00:53:57,924 --> 00:54:00,827
Almighty Cha didn't come after all.

624
00:54:00,827 --> 00:54:03,115
I wanted to see him in his swimsuit.

625
00:54:03,115 --> 00:54:08,279
This is why he's called a nerd.
He doesn't know how to have fun.

626
00:54:08,279 --> 00:54:11,425
Maybe Orabang can't swim?

627
00:54:16,381 --> 00:54:19,109
We came all the way here, so
it'll be disappointing to just leave.

628
00:54:19,109 --> 00:54:23,112
Let's make a nice memory for Orabang.

629
00:54:25,432 --> 00:54:29,303
A human being's mind
has infinite power.

630
00:54:30,356 --> 00:54:33,148
The mind controls the universe.

631
00:54:33,148 --> 00:54:36,655
The mind controls your body.

632
00:54:36,655 --> 00:54:40,364
I'm at a small temple in a deep mountain.

633
00:54:40,364 --> 00:54:42,936
No matter what anyone says, I am...

634
00:54:42,936 --> 00:54:45,371
Let's swim, Orabang!

635
00:54:48,997 --> 00:54:50,377
I can't see anything.

636
00:54:50,377 --> 00:54:51,914
I can't hear anything.

637
00:54:51,914 --> 00:54:54,294
This is a temple in a mountain.

638
00:54:55,626 --> 00:54:57,756
I can't help it.
We should just leave.

639
00:54:57,756 --> 00:55:00,843
Orabang won't even swim.
I'm bored.

640
00:55:00,843 --> 00:55:02,138
We're leaving?

641
00:55:02,721 --> 00:55:05,055
We have to return the life vest.
Take it off.

642
00:55:05,055 --> 00:55:07,180
Really? We're really leaving?

643
00:55:07,180 --> 00:55:09,229
Yes, we should get
there early and practice.

644
00:55:09,229 --> 00:55:10,897
I need to spread my spirit.

645
00:55:10,897 --> 00:55:15,698
A famous timpani player I've only
heard of is coming. I need to practice.

646
00:55:15,698 --> 00:55:17,981
That's right!

647
00:55:17,981 --> 00:55:20,696
Now you're thinking like a normal person.

648
00:55:29,538 --> 00:55:32,507
Why is it next to the beach,
of all places?

649
00:55:33,208 --> 00:55:37,245
Yoo Jin won't have to go
in the water, will he?

650
00:55:46,358 --> 00:55:47,692
Sun-Young!

651
00:55:49,054 --> 00:55:51,852
My goodness, what brought you here?

652
00:55:52,331 --> 00:55:54,605
You meant it
when you said you'd open a cafe.

653
00:55:54,605 --> 00:55:56,186
Is it fun?

654
00:55:56,186 --> 00:55:59,579
It is quite fun to hear about my child
from other people.

655
00:55:59,579 --> 00:56:01,247
Have a seat.

656
00:56:02,249 --> 00:56:04,448
You pretty much abandoned your child...

657
00:56:04,448 --> 00:56:06,520
Why are you being so dramatic now?

658
00:56:06,520 --> 00:56:08,544
Can you give me a cup of coffee?

659
00:56:08,544 --> 00:56:10,957
A cup of Americano, please.

660
00:56:12,119 --> 00:56:14,427
- Is Yoo Jin doing well?
- Of course.

661
00:56:14,427 --> 00:56:16,456
He went to Yoon Yi Song Music Festival,

662
00:56:16,456 --> 00:56:18,962
but I'm nervous
because it's by the beach.

663
00:56:18,962 --> 00:56:20,631
He won't have a reason
to go in the water.

664
00:56:20,631 --> 00:56:22,976
He can't stand planes or ships.

665
00:56:22,976 --> 00:56:24,404
Right?

666
00:56:24,404 --> 00:56:26,341
Is he getting treatments?

667
00:56:26,341 --> 00:56:29,932
According to Dr. Kim, it's been
a while since he stopped by.

668
00:56:30,470 --> 00:56:32,726
It looks like there isn't much to expect
from a doctor's treatment.

669
00:56:32,726 --> 00:56:35,396
It looks like
he's on some hypnotherapy.

670
00:56:38,751 --> 00:56:41,433
The side effects from
the accident are too serious.

671
00:56:48,280 --> 00:56:50,077
Are you just going to leave him like this?

672
00:56:50,077 --> 00:56:52,065
It'll be hard for him to become
a conductor this way.

673
00:56:52,065 --> 00:56:55,268
I told you that Yoo Jin made
a debut as a conductor.

674
00:56:55,268 --> 00:56:57,539
But it's just a college orchestra.

675
00:56:57,539 --> 00:56:59,172
It'll be hard for him to develop more.

676
00:56:59,172 --> 00:57:01,380
Someone who dreams of becoming
a conductor can't go abroad?

677
00:57:01,380 --> 00:57:03,301
That again!

678
00:57:04,411 --> 00:57:08,081
It's a waste to leave Yoo Jin to rot.

679
00:57:08,081 --> 00:57:09,683
I can give job trainings for him.

680
00:57:09,683 --> 00:57:14,654
I told you that Yoo Jin has no interest
other than conducting.

681
00:57:14,654 --> 00:57:16,790
Samhan Electronics is our family business.

682
00:57:16,790 --> 00:57:18,692
I've expanded it this much,

683
00:57:18,692 --> 00:57:21,355
so I want to give it
to someone I trust.

684
00:57:21,355 --> 00:57:24,696
If it's Yoo Jin, I know I can leave it to him.

685
00:57:49,094 --> 00:57:50,971
Orabang, isn't it cool?

686
00:57:50,971 --> 00:57:53,718
He looks amazing even when
he's in the water.

687
00:57:56,268 --> 00:57:59,370
What's with going underwater?
I knew he wanted to have fun.

688
00:58:14,119 --> 00:58:16,118
Something is not right, Lak.

689
00:58:16,118 --> 00:58:18,761
What could go wrong in
such shallow water?

690
00:58:22,822 --> 00:58:24,638
My body...

691
00:58:24,638 --> 00:58:26,726
it's not moving.

692
00:58:28,535 --> 00:58:32,505
Did I fall into... in the ocean again?

693
00:58:34,640 --> 00:58:36,442
Am I going to...

694
00:58:36,442 --> 00:58:38,476
die like this?

695
00:58:41,230 --> 00:58:43,120
Orabang!
